HEADWORD: Fragmentariness
<hw>Frag"men*ta*ri*ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The quality or property
of being in fragments, or broken pieces; incompleteness; want of
continuity.</def> <rj><au>G. Eliot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fragmentary</ent>⟦br⟧
